033255", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "catalog", "usnd"], "subject": ["united states", "pierce", "river falls", "newspapers", "wisconsin", "saint croix", "river falls (wis.)"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T07:41:00.369Z", "title": "River Falls journal", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn85033255/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2023270568/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1872", "dates": ["[1872 TO 2019]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began in 1872. Publisher: A. Morse & Son, <1874>. Published also in a weekly ed., Aug. 5, 1873-June 24, 1874. Editors: S.R. Morse, Feb. 23, 1911-Jan. 1, 1925; E.H. Smith, July 5, 1928-June 13, 1929; C.E. Chubb, April 5, 1945-June 27, 1957; G.M. Kremer, July 4, 1957-July 24, 1958; J.V. Griggs, Aug. 23, 1984- Semiweekly issues distinguished as 1st and 2nd editions, July 22, 1873-Mar. 20, 1874. Supplements accompany some issues. Available on microfilm from The State Historical Society of Wisconsin. Merged with: Hudson Star Observer, and: New Richmond News, to form: Star-Observer. Vol. 16, No. 9 (August 23, 1872); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 13, 2023). Vol. 69, No. 45 (December 31, 1925) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 13, 2023). Hudson star-observer New Richmond news (New Richmond, Wis. : 2000) Star-Observer (Red Wing, Minn.)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:09.301Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023270568/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "pierce", "river falls", "saint croix", "wisconsin"], "number": ["2023270588", "2837-1720", "1375679161", "online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2023270568"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "river falls journal (river falls, 